  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nCurrently, our archival service works on the following premise:\r\n```\r\nIf we receive a block with a slot that is also the end of an epoch, archive data\r\n```\r\nIf a proposer fails to create a block at that slot (called a skip slot in the eth2 protocol), then we will _never_ archive data for that slot! Some users of our API reported some data missing for various epochs, which is something we can resolve.\r\n\r\nA solution would be to instead keep track of the last epoch archived in the archiver service, and then if we receive a block eventually that has an epoch > the last archived, we archive data immediately. ",
